text: IF  THEN Information must be presented within a coherent framework to maintain relevance and utility.
IF  THEN Media consumption should actively seek connections between disparate information fragments.
IF  THEN When faced with limitations, repurpose available tools to meet immediate needs.
IF  THEN Assess the fundamental capabilities of a technology before expecting it to replace established practices.
IF  THEN Always analyze a technology's inherent predispositions and historical context before implementation
IF  THEN Prioritize understanding the core purpose of a technology to maximize its potential benefits.
IF  THEN Align technological deployment with strategic objectives to avoid unintended negative consequences.
IF  THEN Visual engagement must be prioritized over verbal exposition to ensure audience retention, even in educational or serious content.
IF  THEN When adapting serious topics for television, the medium's inherent constraints (e.g., frequent cuts, background music) must override traditional discourse standards.
IF  THEN Prioritize visual appeal and entertainment value over substantive content depth in communication
IF  THEN Evaluate information sources based on their impact on cognition, not entertainment value.
IF  THEN Prioritize understanding over engagement in public discourse.
IF  THEN Prioritize deep engagement over passive consumption of media.
IF  THEN Evaluate media's impact on critical thinking and societal depth.
IF  THEN Evaluate the trade-offs between entertainment value and substantive engagement with content.
IF  THEN Maintain vigilance against the incremental erosion of critical thinking through media consumption.
IF  THEN Maintain awareness of global political developments
IF  THEN Evaluate the implications of adopting new technologies
IF  THEN Societies must actively maintain focus to prevent being overwhelmed by distractions.
IF  THEN The balance between freedom and distraction dictates societal health.
IF  THEN Prioritize camera appeal and entertainment value in public communication to gain audience attention.
IF  THEN Substance in communication must be secondary to style to achieve cultural relevance.
IF  THEN Content must be adapted to the's inherent capabilities to effectively influence culture.
IF  THEN Strategic selection of communication methods determines the persuasive power of a message.
IF  THEN Always analyze the metaphorical implications of tools and media when making decisions.
IF  THEN Consider how innovations in tools can challenge and transform existing cultural and cognitive frameworks.
IF  THEN Truth should be communicated using the most appropriate medium to ensure clarity and resonance.
IF  THEN Epistemology is derived from the communication method used to convey information.
IF  THEN Delay judgment until all relevant information is available.
IF  THEN Apply personal experience as a counterargument to proposed ideas.
IF  THEN Withhold knowledge that is irrelevant to the current discussion.
IF  THEN Evaluate new technologies by examining their historical trade-offs, including potential benefits and drawbacks.
IF  THEN Adopt media changes with caution, considering their impact on the quality and value of public discourse.
IF  THEN Employ visual and dramatic elements to simplify complex ideas and ensure retention.
IF  THEN Focus on concise, story-driven presentations to maintain attention in mass media.
